braceletsizeguide.determine_size: A simple way to determine your bracelet size
braceletsizeguide.perfectly_sized: A bracelet is perfectly sized when you measure your wrist and add 1 inch / 2 cm (2 fingers) for the charms. The most popular bracelet size is 7.5 in / 19 cm.
braceletsizeguide.full_charm: A full charm bracelet holds on average 15 to 20 charms depending on size of the bracelet. For bangles and leather bracelets a maximum of 7 to 9 beads are recommended.

ringsizeguide.desc_1: If you are between sizes, order a larger size.
ringsizeguide.desc_2: The most popular ring sizes are 6, 7 & 8
ringsizeguide.desc_3: How to Measure your Ring Size
ringsizeguide.desc_5: Select a ring that properly fits the intended finger and measure the INSIDE diameter of the ring. Choose your right size according to the SIZE CHART.
ringsizeguide.desc_7: Prepare a piece of string (if you don't have string, cut out a strip of paper), a pen, a ruler, and scissors.
ringsizeguide.desc_8: Wrap the piece of string or paper around the base of your ring finger. Wrap around both the base of your finger and your knuckle if your knuckle is noticeably larger than the base of your finger.
ringsizeguide.desc_9: Mark the string or paper at the exact point that it overlaps to make a compete circle around your finger. Do this for where it overlaps on your knuckle as well, if you needed to measure it.
ringsizeguide.desc_10: Unroll the string or paper and place it against a ruler that is divided in millimeters. The length between the two marks on your string or paper meets the ruler is the circumference of your ring finger. Refer to a ring chart to get your ring size. For example, if the circumference measures 62 mm, your ring size is a 10.
